		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Counters on Shelob, EoL<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(2.50)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=17333'>Philly "KingChoke" Kemp</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=17333&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> June 30, 2004</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Inrto:<br />
Hi LotR fans. This is an article on how to kill that nasty Shelob, Eater of Light without having to lose any of your companions. Hope his helps you out.<br />
<br />
<br />
First of all, here is Shelob’s text.<br />
<br />
Title: Shelob, Eater of Light<br />
Twilight Cost: 6<br />
Type: Minion : Spider<br />
Strength 8<br />
Vitality: 8<br />
Site Number: 8<br />
Text: Fierce: When you play Shelob, you may play a (Gollum) possession from your draw deck.<br />
Shelob is strength + 3 for each minions stacked on a (Gollum) possession.<br />
<br />
Ok. This is a whopping 8 vitality minion. It is almost impossible to kill her in archery.<br />
The way Shelob gets her strength bonus is the card Web. It allows you to stack up to 3 (Gollum) creatures (which Shelob is) and Orcs on each Web (which they are not unique).<br />
Plus, you get to play back the (Gollum) minions in the Shadow phase. This means infinite<br />
Shelob. <br />
She gets her strength bonus from all the other Shelob and orcs stacked on web. She could get to an automatic strength of 48 without any pumps.<br />
I know, this is an annoying spider. But if you read this article, you may find good ways to put Shelob defense in your deck.<br />
<br />
Ok, her is my article.<br />
<br />
 <br />
You know how annoying it is when your opponent gets out a stinking 30-some strength <br />
Shelob and overwhelms 2 companions every turn. This happened to me once at a tourney (I still ended up beating him though with my Uruks) that really made me mad. So, I started thinking of ways to counter that darn spider. BUG SPRAY anyone. No, just kidding. But I did come up with a few ways to counter the annoying spider. I’m sure you all have heard of most of these but this should help out the newbies. I mean, how would you like to be new to the game and lose 2 companions every skirmish phase. Here are<br />
some ways…<br />
<br />
What Are They:<br />
<br />
Title: What Are They<br />
Type: Event<br />
Text: Maneuver: Spot a Ranger to discard a roaming minion.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
This is an awesome card to use against Shelob. Since lots of decks run Rangers (Boromir<br />
Aragorn, Ranger of the North), this should be a fairly easy way of adding Shelob protection. Since Shelob is roaming to site 8, you could discard her in the maneuver phase and not worry about having to fight her. She is not roaming on but 1 site in the whole game, so you have plenty of time to use this card.<br />
<br />
Smeagol, Bearer of Great Secrets:<br />
<br />
Title: Smeagol, Bearer of Great Secrets<br />
Twilight Cost: 0<br />
Type: Companion<br />
Strength: 3<br />
Vitality: 4<br />
Text: Ring-bound: Every time the Fellowship moves, place a unbound companion in the dead pile. Regroup: If Smeagol is the Ring-bearer, add 2 burdens to discard each minion.<br />
<br />
<br />
Ok. The first part of his text has nothing to do with Shelob. The first part of his text is the draw back, BUT, you can dodge that text by playing all Ring-bound companions:<br />
His regroup text is what gets rid of Shelob. Since you get first Regroup action, you can add 2 burdens before your opponent gets a chance to stack his Shelob/Orcs on his or her Web. Usually in this deck you run burden removal. This gets rid of the burdens that Smeagol adds to get rid of Shelbo and her pray.<br />
<br />
Boromir’s Gauntlets<br />
<br />
Title: Boromir’s Gauntlets<br />
Twilight Cost: 1<br />
Type: Possession<br />
Text: Bearer must be a Gondor Man. Exert bearer to cancel a skirmish involving him. Any shadow player may remove one to prevent this<br />
<br />
All thought this is not the best way to counter Shelob, it still can keep you alive for a while. As long as your opponent doesn’t have any twilight, you can cancel the skirmishes involving Shelob.<br />
<br />
Escape<br />
<br />
Title: Escape<br />
Twilight Cost: 0<br />
Type: Condition<br />
Vitality Bonus: +1<br />
Text: Bearer must be an unbound hobbit. Limit one per bearer. Skirmish: Exert bearer twice to cancel a skirmish involving bearer. Any shadow player may remove 1 to prevent this.<br />
<br />
Just like the Gaunlets.<br />
<br />
Dervorin<br />
<br />
Title: Dervorin<br />
Twilight Cost: 2<br />
Type: Companion : Man<br />
Strength: 6<br />
Vitality: 3<br />
Text: At the start of each regroup phase, if you have only 4 cards in hand, you may spot another (Gondor) man to discard a minion.<br />
<br />
This is a good way to get of Shelob herself. Although you still have to fight her, if Dervorin survives, you can discard her in the regroup.<br />
<br />
<br />
These are just some ways I thought up of. Of course there are Derufin to get rid of shadow possessions (good way of getting rid of Web). And the Gondor Bowmen/Double Shot/ Reckless We Rode to get rid of her in the archery, but these were a few other ideas.<br />
<br />
Hope they helped.<br />
<br />
&quot;KingChoke&quot;<br />
<br />
